The deposed Emir of Kano, Lamido Sanusi arrived the Murtala Mohammed Airport in Lagos midnight Friday. Airport sources told LEADERSHIP that the former emir left Abuja airport aboard a private jet owned by Quits Aviation at about 9pm. He landed at the Murtala Muhammed Airport (MMA), Lagos at some minutes past 10pm at Quits Aviation Terminal, one of the Private hangars at the airport. It was gathered that the Emir had specifically told his aides that he would not be willing to talk to media on his arrival at the airport. As at the time of filing this report, it was not clear why the emir was coming to Lagos, but reports on Tuesday claimed that his family and other associates were already in Lagos, ahead of his coming.